                <h1>23 days since Indianapolis</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/661a5e1e-66bf-4a8a-a754-34d774fe4d46.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="When&#x20;the&#x20;Blue&#x20;Devils&#x20;defeated&#x20;James&#x20;Madison&#x20;in&#x20;David&#x20;Cutcliffe&#x2019;s&#x20;first&#x20;game&#x20;as&#x20;head&#x20;coach,&#x20;Duke&#x20;students&#x20;chanted&#x20;&#x201C;BCS&#x21;&#x20;BCS&#x21;&#x201D;&#x20;at&#x20;the&#x20;players." class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            When the Blue Devils defeated James Madison in David Cutcliffe’s first game as head coach, Duke students chanted “BCS! BCS!” at the players.

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/chase-olivierichronicle-file-photo">Chase Olivieri/Chronicle File Photo</a> |
                                                                                                                                The Chronicle
                                                                            </figcaption>
                                </aside>
                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/gabe-starosta">Gabe Starosta</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">April 28, 2010 | 4:00am EDT</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2010/04/23-days-indianapolis" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2010/04/23-days-indianapolis&amp;text=23 days since Indianapolis" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=23%20days%20since%20Indianapolis%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2010%2F04%2F23-days-indianapolis" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Every day, it gets a little harder to believe. Duke won a national championship, and I was there. I was on the court two minutes after Gordon Hayward missed that shot that no Duke fan will ever forget. As the players celebrated, I told Brian Zoubek that I was a Duke senior and asked him what this title was like for him, and as he answered, he put his arm around my shoulders and hunched down&mdash;really, he could have sat down, since he&rsquo;s 17 inches taller than me&mdash;and we chummed it up as if we were just a pair of Duke students. And the day the Blue Devils beat West Virginia, two hours before the Michigan-State-Butler game, I sat on Coach K&rsquo;s stool. Yes, it&rsquo;s as cool as you think.</p>
<p></p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p></p>
<p>And all along&mdash;as Duke breezed through Jacksonville, Houston, and eventually, Indianapolis, too&mdash;I had to keep asking myself: Is it worth it?</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p>Because for every other Duke fan aside from the players, the coaching staff and their massive entourage, this Blue Devil run to the Final Four was a dream come true. But for me, the sports editor of The Chronicle, it meant a hell of a lot more work than I had signed up for, just as my college days were coming to a close.</p>
<p></p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p></p>
<p>In the end, it probably was worth it. The newspaper on the day of April 6&mdash;the one with the wonderful photo of Jon Scheyer hugging Lance Thomas, with the bolded headline, UN-FOUR-GETTABLE&mdash;was a beauty, and it featured my story prominently. My name is on t-shirts, for God&rsquo;s sake. Writing that story was an honor, and I value that more than having attended the game itself.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
                            

<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="58dfdea1a4">
    <h3>Get Overtime, all Duke athletics</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <form action="//dukechronicle.us4.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=c49dc69f492af7f2727860d0b&amp;id=58dfdea1a4" method="post">
